# Deployment — who THIS project is

The **last identity layer** (canon SA-025). RasaOS knows it's the substrate; the
Element knows it's a `<kind>` for `<subject>`; **you fill in what this specific
project is.** Answer these so any session — human or agent — knows the full
picture the moment it loads.

- **Project:** [what is this? e.g. "an iOS product"]
- **For:** [company / owner — e.g. "VSI"]
- **Platform:** [e.g. iOS, web, backend, none]
- **Goal:** [what this project is trying to achieve]

> This file is **project-owned** and never overwritten on Element upgrade. If
> your tenant declares this (purpose / owner / platform), copy it here.

**Composed identity** — the answer to "who are you?" reads across all three
layers, e.g.:

> *"I am a RasaOS **domain** for **coding** an **iOS product** for a company
> called **VSI**."*

(The RasaOS + element layers come from `.claude/rasa-identity.md`; this file is
the deployment layer. `/whoami` renders the composed statement.)
